description.description_string: Guideline 36 controller for VAV terminal unit with reheat
Local record for VAV damper with lumped flow resistance
Local record for coil with lumped flow resistance

expression.simple_expression:
"

Description

This template represents a VAV terminal unit with reheat.

The possible equipment configurations are enumerated in the table below. The user may refer to ASHRAE (2018) for further details. The first option displayed in bold characters corresponds to the default configuration.

ComponentSupported configurationNote
VAV damper Pressure independent damper
Modulating damper
Reheat coil Hot water coil
Modulating electric heating coil
No coil 		By default a two-way modulating valve is considered for a hot water coil. Alternative options for the control valve are available.
Controller Open loop controller
ASHRAE Guideline 36 controller

References

  • ASHRAE, 2018. Guideline 36-2018, High-Performance Sequences of Operation for HVAC Systems. Atlanta, GA.
"
